<HEADLINE>
DAUGHTER PAINTS A LOVING PORTRAIT OF DAD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICK ORLOV 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Vice President Al Gore, months after clinching the
job, was formally chosen on Wednesday night as the Democratic
nominee for president after his eldest daughter described him in a
loving tribute as a man who ``wants to see goodness prevail.''
