<P>
   HIKER-HUT-ACCESS (In the White Mountains National Forest, N.H.)
_ Over slick boulders, across too-narrow bridges and through mud
three hikers in wheelchairs and two on crutches braved a 12-hour
struggle up the Gale Head trail. Their destination, the Gale Head
Hut at an elevation of 4,300 feet, which has just been rebuilt by
the Appalachian Mountain Club. During the process, some had
ridiculed the idea that the club would go to the expense of making
the hut handicapped-accessible, since no one in a wheelchair was
ever going to get there. They were wrong, it turns out. By Carey
Goldberg.
</P>
<P>
   STEP-CHILDREN (Undated) _ Children raised by stepmothers are
likely to have less health care, less education and less money
spent on their food than children raised by their biological
mothers, three studies by a Princeton economist have found. By
Tamar Lewin.
</P>
