<P>
   ROTHKO _ HOUSTON _ After undergoing a $1.2 million renovation
and a major restoration to the paintings, the Rothko Chapel in
Houston is recently reopening. We visit this meditative landmark
and talk to the conservator who unraveled the mystery behind why
Rothko's stunning black paintings were slowly turning white. (Van
Ryzin, Austin American-Statesman).
