   &UR; AS THE MOON TURNS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (600 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By BOB BERMAN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Did you know that the sun is 450,000 times brighter than the
full moon? That its surface is as dark as asphalt? That it ignores
Earth's tilt and revolves around the globe in the same plane as the
planets? Find out some other interesting, little-known facts about
Earth's natural satellite in this astronomy feature. One color
slide is available. (slugged: BC-MOON-DISCOVER-$ADV09-ART-NYTSF)
