Internet routinely use shopbots _ software agents that
automatically canvass the Internet looking for the cheapest price
for a given product. Now e-businesses are deploying agents of their
own. For example, the online retailer Buy.com is reportedly using
price-comparison software that automatically adjusts its prices to
undercut competitors' prices. But if online sellers deploy
pricebots, will the result be digital mayhem? A report. By Jeffrey
O. Kephart and Amy R. Greenwald.
</P>
