<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-17 14:02 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4590 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r s BC-FBN-49ERS-YOUNG-HNS &LR;      08-17 0304
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-49ERS-YOUNG-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     RETIRED QUARTERBACK VISITS NINERS' CAMP 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By KEVIN LYNCH  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   STOCKTON, Calif. _ Shirt untucked, shoes untied and khaki pants
ruffled, former San Francisco 49ers quarterback Steve Young very
much looked like a man reveling in retirement.
</P>
<P>
   Young, 38, visited his old team at the request of coach Steve
Mariucci. Young didn't sound quite convincing when he said he
didn't miss football.
</P>
<P>
   Instead of leading a team of 52 players, Young is now looking
after a team of one. ``A lot of my time is being married,'' said
Young, who married former model Barbara Graham in March. ``(I'm)
making sure she's happy and settled. I'm the cook. I'm the one who
has to take care of a lot of little things because my wife has some
risks in her pregnancy. It's really different to serve someone
else. It's a good lesson.''
</P>
<P>
   The only news Young has made lately has been his invocation at
the recent Republican National Convention in Philadelphia and his
well-publicized tiff with quarterback Jeff Garcia.
</P>
<P>
   Young regretted dipping his head during his prayer at the
Republican convention, because it revealed his bald spot. Otherwise
he enjoyed the experience. Still, Young reiterated that he would
not seek political office.
</P>
<P>
   He was dragged into the news when Garcia recently said Young
wasn't much of a help to him after Garcia assumed Young's starter's
role last season. After exchanging messages, the two men talked
briefly following Wednesday's morning practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think there was much to straighten out,'' Young said.
``I don't like to firehouse people with a lot of information
especially when you're trying to play. . . . If he had needed more,
I would have given it to him.''
</P>
</TEXT>
