Philadelphia two weeks ago _ was decidedly declasse this week on
the coast where trends are born. When the Republicans met in
Philly, all things Texan and Bush were cool, hinting at the
possibility that a Bush win might make Texas trendier than it has
been since Urban Cowboy days. It was a different story out here,
where Texas and Bush took it on the chin at the souvenir stands,
from the podium and when the states lined up to vote. (Herman,
