   &UR; SCIENCE &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SF-QUAKE (Undated) _ A notorious fault that runs through
Berkeley, Calif., may not be capable of generating a large
earthquake on its own, scientists report Thursday. Using a new
technique based on measurements taken from space and from deep
within the earth, the researchers conclude that the Hayward fault
is creeping steadily along its entire width and depth, relieving
the tectonic stresses. However, people who live near the fault are
still in danger of heavy damage from quakes along faults nearby. By
Sandra Blakeslee.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SKIN-CANCER (Undated) _ The stem cells for the skin, long
thought to reside in the basement layer of the skin, in fact hide
out in the hair follicles, researchers report. This is important
for understanding how the skin heals and may also shed light on the
causes of skin cancer. By Nicholas Wade.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-LASER-NUKES (Washington) _ Development of the world's most
powerful laser, that could monitor the nation's nuclear arsenal
without testing, could cost nearly three times its original $1
billion price tag, congressional auditors say. By James Glanz.
</P>
