 By JOEL BROWN 
 c. 2000 Joel Brown 
<TEXT>
<P>
   VH1 has scored big ratings with its ``Behind the Music'' series
and other kinds of documentary programming. Its latest effort is
``VH1 Confidential,'' debuting at 10 tonight, a kind of ``Behind
the Music Without the Boring Parts.''
</P>
<P>
   The show will explore the mysteries and myths of rock 'n' roll _
maybe they can get to the truth of Dylan's motorcycle accident. But
tonight's choice is more predictable _ one more rehash of the
controversy surrounding Kurt Cobain's suicide, which some factions
inevitably claim was murder. This is one second gunman theory to
which we'll say thanks but no thanks.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HIGHLIGHTS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Big Brother,'' CBS at 8: Karen's gone, but we still have to
listen to poor love-starved ``cuddle bunny'' Brittany _ cruel and
unusual punishment indeed.
</P>
<P>
   ``Who Wants to Be a Millionaire,'' ABC at 8: Regis Philbin
hosts.
</P>
<P>
   ``Buffy the Vampire Slayer,'' WB at 8: The Scooby Gang has to go
back to the ghostly ruins of their high school to prevent the
apocalypse one more time. Rerun.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mysterious Ways,'' Pax at 8: Corporate synergy between NBC and
its new toy, the Pax network, means that this show moves over to
the latter beginning tonight with the pilot. Adrian Pasdar and Rae
Dawn Chong star in a series that might be called ``Touched By An
X-File.'' We're not sure if we call this a rerun or not.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dharma &AMP; Greg,'' ABC at 9: Straight-laced Greg ponders the
meaning of his lawyerly existence. Rerun.
</P>
<P>
   ``Frasier,'' NBC at 9: Frasier hosts a bachelor party for Donny
and swears he won't be a stuffy fussbudget as usual. What are the
odds? Rerun.
</P>
<P>
   ``Angel,'' WB at 9: Faith (Eliza Dushku) gets hired by the evil
lawyer cabal to take on Angel one last time.
</P>
<P>
   ``NYPD Blue,'' ABC at 10: Russell puts herself on the line for
Kirkendall. Rerun.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FAMILY FARE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Race to Freedom: The Underground Railroad,'' Fox Family
Channel at 8: Janet Bailey, Courtney B. Vance, Dawnn Lewis, Glynn
Turman and Tim Reid star in this 1994 telling of the heroic tale of
four escaped slaves in the 1850s.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CABLE CAST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Ali-Frasier I ... One Nation Divisible,'' HBO at 8:
Documentary explores America's social divisions circa 1970 through
the lens of the first Ali-Frasier fight.
</P>
<P>
   ``Gilligan's Island'' marathon, Nick at 9: A true three-hour
tour to help you warm up for Wednesday's three-hour ``Survivor''
finale.
</P>
<P>
   ``E! True Hollywood Story,'' E! at 9: Somehow, the cable channel
manages to wring two hours out of the backstage story behind 1960s
sitcom ``Bewitched,'' including the real life drama of the two
Darrins, Dick York and Dick Sargent.
</P>
<P>
   ``Behind the Music,'' VH1 at 9: Speaking of wringing out, VH1
also manages to stretch the story of the short-lived 1980s band The
Bangles to an hour.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Right Temptation,'' HBO at 9: This R-rated 2000 cheapo
noir flick about a female private eye involved in messy sexual
intrigues has the potential to be so bad it's good. Consider the
cast: Rebecca De Mornay, Kiefer Sutherland, Dana Delany, Adam
Baldwin, Joanna Cassidy.
</P>
<P>
   ``Real World,'' MTV at 10: It's Mardi Gras time for the New
Orleans cast. They get to party with vampire author Anne Rice and
ride on her float in one of the wild parades.
</P>
<P>
   ``Bull,'' TNT at 10: More outrages on Wall Street in this new
drama series. Stanley Tucci stars.
</P>
<P>
   ``Beggars and Choosers,'' Showtime at 10: Control of the network
changes hands in this Hollywood satire.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LATE NIGHT TALK &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Late Show with David Letterman,'' CBS at 11:35: Jon Favreau
and musical guest Stone Temple Pilots.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tonight Show with Jay Leno,'' NBC at 11:35: Kirsten Dunst.
</P>
<P>
   ``Politically Incorrect with Bill Maher,'' ABC at 12:05: Actor
Joe Rogan.
</P>
<P>
   ``Late, Late Show with Craig Kilborn,'' CBS at 12:35 a.m.: Kyle
MacLachlan.
</P>
<P>
   ``Late Night with Conan O'Brien,'' NBC at 12:35: TBA. &QL;
</P>
