   &UR; `WHY HAS THE PRESIDENT BEEN SILENT?' ANGRY RUSSIANS ASK &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PUTIN-FIRING-LINE-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MOSCOW _ ``Why has the president been silent?'' demanded the
daily Komsomolskaya Pravda in two-inch high red letters on its
front page Thursday. The newspaper asks why vacationing Vladimir
Putin took five days to make his first brief comment on the sinking
of the Kursk nuclear submarine to the bottom of the Barents Sea,
while finding time to appoint new ambassadors to Jamaica and Chile.
Just before the presidential election in March Putin dressed up in
a military pilot's uniform to fly in a fighter-bomber. He even,
ironically, spent a night underwater in a nuclear submarine. It is
these images which are now coming back to haunt Putin....By Patrick
Cockburn, The Independent &QL;
