<P>
   RUSSIA-SUBMARINE (Moscow) _ In frantic efforts against
increasingly hopeless odds to save the crew of the sunken nuclear
submarine Kursk, Russian rescue teams tried and failed through
another stormy night and throughout Thursday to lock onto a rear
escape hatch of the shattered vessel. New reports emerged of
catastrophic damage to the hull, suggesting the ship went down in a
torrent of fire and flooding that may have killed or mortally
wounded everyone aboard. The growing prospect that the crew may be
beyond rescue, making the sinking of the Kursk Russia's worst
peacetime naval disaster, generated a wave of recriminations
through the Russian news media, much of it aimed at the military,
but also at the new Russian president, Vladimir Putin, who remained
on vacation at the Black Sea resort of Sochi. By Patrick E. Tyler.
