<P>
   SCI-SKIN-CANCER (Undated) _ Maybe it's not like discovering a
new bone in the human body. But many basic facts about human
physiology are still unknown, such as the source of the new skin
cells that replace those shed in every day's wear and tear. And
those source or stem cells now turn out to be hiding in the roots
of the hair. The finding, if confirmed, would lead to better
understanding of how the skin heals, as well as to insights into
basal skin cell carcinoma, one of the commonest kinds of cancer. By
Nicholas Wade.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``s'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BOX-IBF-TRIAL (Newark, N.J.) _ The founder of the International
Boxing Federation, the only sanctioning body for boxing based in
the United States, was acquitted on charges that he took bribes
from promoters and managers to give good rankings to their boxers.
Robert W. Lee, who founded the IBF as an alternative to sanctioning
bodies he considered corrupt, was cleared by a federal jury here of
the most serious charges of bribery. He was found guilty on some
charges, including tax evasion, money laundering and interstate
travel in aid of racketeering, and could face some prison time. By
Ronald Smothers.
</P>
