scientist at the Los Alamos National Laboratory, accused of
illegally moving the secret data to an unsecure computer and
portable computer tapes, some of which are missing, with the intent
to harm the United States. By James Sterngold.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-GRAND-JURY (Washington) _ In a development that is not
surprising but is nonetheless ill-timed for Democrats, a new grand
jury has been seated to consider evidence against President Clinton
in the scandal over his relationship with Monica Lewinsky. The
selection of the grand jury actually took place several weeks ago.
It came out Thursday as government officials disclosed that the
special three-judge panel overseeing the office of Robert Ray, the
independent counsel investigating the president, had determined
that Ray's office should not be shut down. By David Johnston.
