<HEADER>
A4904 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u e BC-TV-OZ-HNS &LR;      08-17 0218
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-OZ-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HBO'S LATEST EPISODE OF PRISON DRAMA REVEALS EVEN MORE THAN USUAL
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By MIKE McDANIEL 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
The HBO prison drama ``Oz'' routinely shows people being stabbed,
punched, raped, sodomized and murdered. Nary an episode goes by
without some frontal male nudity.
<TEXT>
<P>
   But Wednesday's episode crossed the line, showing something not
seen on American TV before: a naked man urinating in a bucket.
</P>
<P>
   The scene, with actor Christopher Meloni, left nothing to the
imagination. It was not shot from the rear. It was not masked by
artful editing or a well-positioned set prop.
</P>
<P>
   ``There was no artificial tubing or anything,'' Tom Fontana, the
show's creator and executive producer, said Thursday. ``When I was
writing the scene, I called Chris and told him what I wanted to do.
He said, `OK, not a problem.'''
</P>
<P>
   The truth about anything, Fontana said, is that it's open to
interpretation.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's like anything in life. Some people would consider it
gratuitous, some people would consider it salacious, and some would
say it's provocative. For me, it's about life. It's about what
people do.''
</P>
<P>
   The scene never came up for discussion with HBO, Fontana said.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's why we love them.''
</P>
<P>
   XXX ENDOF STORY
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
