   INSIDE STORIES PROMOTED ON PAGE 1:
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SKIN-CELLS (Undated) _ The source of the new skin cells that
replace those shed in every day's wear and tear turn out to be
hiding in the roots of the hair. The finding, if confirmed, could
lead to better understanding of how the skin heals as well as to
insights into basal cell carcinoma, a common skin cancer. By
Nicholas Wade.
</P>
<P>
   (EDS: Skedded earlier at SCI-SKIN-CANCER.)
