<P>
   FBN-LEWIS-FINE (Undated) _ The National Football League has
fined Baltimore Ravens linebacker Ray Lewis $250,000 for lying to
police about an incident that resulted in the stabbing deaths of
two men outside an Atlanta nightclub after the Super Bowl in
January. The fine is the largest ever levied under the NFL's
personal conduct policy. By Mike Freeman.
