<HEADLINE>
TWO NAMED AT N.E. NEWSPAPER GROUP 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ The Boston Globe and its parent, The New York Times
Co., Thursday named two marketing executives to key positions in
advertising and circulation for the New England Newspaper Group.
</P>
<P>
   Mary Jane Patrone, senior vice president of sales and marketing
at the Globe, will add to her duties the same role at the New
England Newspaper Group. The group includes the Globe and the
Worcester Telegram &AMP; Gazette, as well as Community Newsdealers and
Globe Speciality Products, a direct-marketing unit. Patrone will be
responsible for all advertising sales and services, marketing and
promotion for the publications in the group.
</P>
<P>
   At the same time, Yasmin Namini, vice president of circulation
at The New York Times, will become senior vice president of
consumer marketing for the New England operations. She will also be
senior vice president of ciculation at the Globe, overseeing all
circulation sales and services.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are proud that the Globe is the dominant mass medium in New
England and we intend to keep it that way,'' said Richard H.
Gilman, the Globe's publisher and president of the New England
Newspaper Group. ``Given the magnitude and the potential, it is
important that we fill these posts with individuals of the highest
caliber.''
</P>
<P>
   Patrone has been with the Globe since 1976. Namini joined the
Times in 1984; from 1986 to 1989, she managed the Times' home
delivery office in Boston.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
