   GROWTH (Phoenix) - The real estate industry holds a fund-raiser
to finance an expected $4 million campaign to carpet bomb the
Phoenix area with ads against the Sierra Club growth initiative.
The campaign appears to be the most expensive among this year's
ballot initiatives but is by no means the most expensive ever.
