<P>
   INVEST-LINUX (Undated) _ Remember Linus Torvalds? Last year, the
Linux operating system he created was going to revolutionize the
software industry, do more damage to Microsoft than the Justice
Department and make investors rich. This year, Linux stocks have
been in a prolonged downward spiral and Torvalds has been replaced
on magazine covers by Napster's Shawn Fanning as the technologist
most likely to wreak havoc on traditional ways of doing business.
By Danny Hakim.
