<P>
   __ At last, a new motif in Bristol, Conn. What an ESPN press
release calls a ``multi-purpose, state-of-the-art studio'' _
another Staples Center? _ will debut on the 3 p.m. ``SportsCenter''
and strangely look and act as functionally as the Fox Sports Net's
``National Sports Report'' set. It'll also be used for most all
other ESPN studio shows. Easy on the eyes? Probably not. But the
old ESPN wood-and-nails studio, in use since 1994, was set for the
scrap heap upon its debut, so the change is long overdue. &QL;
