<SLUG> BC-FBC-CSUN-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CSUN DEFENSE SHARP EARLY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JILL PAINTER  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ So it is too early to praise the Cal State
Northridge defense. But if Thursday's first practice in full pads
is any indication, the Matadors offense can rest a little easier
this season.
</P>
<P>
   Linebacker-turned-safety Isaac Gardner had two interceptions in
the morning practice and defensive back Martin Bacon had a
monstrous hit and interception on consecutive plays.
</P>
<P>
   ``Defensively, we did great,'' CSUN coach Jeff Kearin said.
``Early in training camp and early in practice, the defense is
usually ahead of the offense. But clearly, our defense is playing
great.''
</P>
<P>
   Matadors linebacker coach Terrance Johnson has what Kearin
tabbed the most-improved group on the field. Cos Abercrombie _ who
is moving from weak-side to strong-side linebacker _ returns, as
does middle linebacker Lewis Blanton. Pieter Keus, a sophomore who
played on special teams last season, will start at weak-side.
Abercrombie and Blanton had a combined 89 tackles.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's exciting having Cos back,'' Johnson said. ``And it's
excellent having Lewis back with Pieter Keus coming in. They're
running around making plays. To me, it's excellent to have a group
of guys who know just what the system is and what we expect.''
</P>
<P>
   The linebacker corps also has depth. True freshman Ben Lorier _
a Westlake High product _ could play this season, along with Donald
Curry, a redshirt freshman, and Jonathan Howard, a junior college
transfer.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel great about the linebacker situation,'' Abercrombie
said. ``There aren't too many linebacker corps anywhere that will
be able to do what we do. I'm dead serious about that. The only
thing that can stop us is ourselves.''
</P>
<P>
   Former All-American Brennen Swanson, who played strong-side last
season, is assisting Johnson. Swanson has a school-record 31 career
sacks and single-season record 15.
</P>
<P>
   __ Zaragoza to attend CSUN: Former Kennedy quarterback Ruben
Zaragoza plans to take classes at CSUN this year. Zaragoza is a
nonqualifier, so he can't practice or play for the Matadors for one
year.
</P>
<P>
   __ Venner ineligible: Fresno State transfer Ramsey Venner _ who
would've started at defensive end _ has been ruled ineligible by
CSUN, according to Kearin. Venner, who's 6-foot-6, 260 pounds, will
redshirt this season and practice with the Matadors.
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury report: There are numerous minor injuries but nothing
serious. Johnny Acosta, Ashcon Madjid and Andrew Holt _ all
offensive linemen _ are nursing injuries. Madjid and Holt have
shoulder injuries and Acosta has a back injury. . . . Tight end Rob
Porter sat out Thursday with a pulled groin. . . . Linebacker Chris
Sweeney has contused ribs. . . . Receiver Jason Stone, who sat out
with food poisoning Wednesday, returned to practice Thursday. . . .
All-American punter Ethan Beck has a minor hamstring injury. . . .
Marcus Hardrick is out with a hip flexor.
</P>
</TEXT>
