<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-LA-POLICE-NYT (moved Tuesday, August 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, August 15
about protests against the Los Angeles Police Department referred
incorrectly to the recent corruption disclosures about the
department's Rampart Division, where more than 20 officers have
been implicated in the fabrication of evidence and the framing of
suspects. The episode is the city's worst corruption scandal in
decades, not merely in a decade.
</P>
<P>
   BC-TEXAS-PAINTER-NYT (moved Tuesday, August 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, August 15
about renewed interest in the painter and author Tom Lea misstated
the site of an episode he painted _ the sinking of the aircraft
carrier Wasp in World War II. It occurred in the Pacific Ocean, not
the North Atlantic.
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-ALBRECHT (moved Saturday, August 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service obituary sent on Saturday, August
12 of the ballerina Angele Albrecht on Sunday referred imprecisely
to the founding of the New York City Ballet by Lincoln Kirstein and
by George Balanchine, for whom Albrecht danced in Hamburg in the
1950's. The company was founded in 1948, before Albrecht began her
professional career, not after she danced for Balanchine.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
