<HEADLINE>
TURMOIL AT UNITED MAY FORCE DELEGATES TO FLEE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS SIEROTY and ALEXA HAUSSLER 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Thousands of delegates in Los Angeles for the
Democratic National Convention are being urged to leave Friday
instead of Sunday to avoid delays caused by a labor dispute at
United Airlines.
</P>
<P>
