<SLUG> BC-NETZERO-AMAZING-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NETZERO FORGES LOCAL ADVERTISING ALLIANCE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROBERT MONROE 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WESTLAKE VILLAGE _ Hoping to expand its core source of revenue,
NetZero announced Thursday its partnership with a producer of local
advertising.
</P>
<P>
   The partnership between the free Internet access provider and
Fairfax, Va.-based Amazing Media means that NetZero subscribers
will now see the site's ubiquitous ads coming from companies in
their own regions.
</P>
<P>
   NetZero Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Mark Goldston
described the deal as a pioneering venture in Internet advertising
akin to ``spot media'' ads seen and heard on local television and
radio stations.
</P>
<P>
   ``For (small businesses), it's like create-your-own-ad,''
Goldston said. ``You're talking about a pretty potent idea.''
Analysts called the agreement a minor, but necessary, development.
</P>
<P>
   ``NetZero is exclusively deriving revenues from e-commerce,''
said Youssef Squali of ING Baring. ``They have to be able to
attract not only national advertisers but local advertisers as
well.''
</P>
<P>
   Small businesses near NetZero users will target them based on
profiling traits picked up by NetZero's zCast feature. The
technology allows the Internet service provider to monitor a Web
surfer's navigation and interests and flash ads from local
companies on the NetZero window onscreen.
</P>
<P>
   Squali said that the strategy's success will be measured further
down the line.
</P>
<P>
   ``The proof is in the pudding, right?'' he said. ``We should be
seeing NetZero making announcements regarding advertisers using
their services.''
</P>
<P>
   Shares of NetZero were up 25 cents to close at $4.94 on moderate
volume Thursday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
